<br>
<b><u>1st rule of any Raid:</u></b> The Leader/Organizer of the raid is the final word, It is not a democracy. They may ask for council, but their decision is final. If you got a problem with that don’t argue during the raid, just deal with it. And then vent later, remember no one is perfect and people will make the wrong decision, running a raid is not easy.<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><u>Loot Rules:</u></b><br>
1) Items will be Can and Will Use, always. Rolls for items will occur at time of drop.<br>
<br>
2) Specific item requests will ignore rule #1. Example: Walli wants a specific charm from Hate's Fury, the 1st drop of that item goes to him. To balance this out though, the person making specific item requests may not roll on other items on that raid on the same loot table as the requested item. If an item CAWU only by that person though, they may get that item. So if a War item only drops, that Walli will use, then he can get it.<br>
<br>
3) Quest Items: Try to know what quests you are interested in before we head to zone so when an item drops we already know who wants it. See rule #2 for specific quest item requests.<br>
<br>
4) Be fair don't hog loots, share the wealth. Basically if you already got an item, don't go rolling on other items till everyone who can use already declined or has gotten something.<br>
<br>
5) Loots that are not no-drop and of no use to anyone on the raid will be vaulted in guild vault for use by others in the guild. Items/Money in vault will be updated by Walli. Any money gained by sale of vaulted items will be kept by the vault and used to reimburse for coffins, gems used for buffage, and any other raid expenses.<br>
<br>
6) Gems, Cash, and other vendor foder items will be sold at end of raid and split.<br>
<br>
<b><u>Loot Tables:</u></b> <br>
Items are on separate loot tables. You can not roll on an item in the same loot table again until all have gotten an item or declined CAWU. Rolls occur only for CAWU, other items are vaulted for guild or sold for guild funds.<br>
<u>Quest Items</u>- ya need it to do a quest it's on this table<br>
<u>Non-Armor drops</u>- weapons, shields, charms, held items, rings,  basically anything that is not clothing/armor<br>
<u>Armor Drops</u>- Head, Feet, Legs, etc...(does not include shields)<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><u>Raid Etiquette:</u></b><br>
1) Wait for assist calls, do not attack, cast or send pet in till the MA calls for assist.<br>
2) Let the ench CC, if the ench needs help they will ask.<br>
3) MA, if you switch targets, call it.<br>
4) Do not wander, only two people that should leave the main group are the puller, and MA.<br>
5) Puller will call for a tag if needed, MA will tag.<br>
6) Pay attention to chat, this can get distracting, but chat keeps us all on the same page as to what is going on.<br>
<br>
<b><u>Raid Rolls:</u></b><br>
The following rolls should be assigned at beginning of raid, may vary a bit depending on specifics of raid.<br>
1) MA – Main Ass(ist)<br>
2) Puller – The go gettum guy<br>
3) CC – Crowd control<br>
4) Slower – duh<br>
5) ML(W) – Master Loot Whore<br>
6) SA/Pealer – Secondary Assist, incase MA goes down … also Pealer, goes and saves the casters from agro.<br>
<br>
<br>
<b><u>Level Restrictions:</u></b> At this time there are no imposed level restricions for Heavy Hand members. Understand the following though, you will probably die and you may not get exp. There will be instances that when going to certian zones that low level characters will cuase severe problems, in those circumstances a level limit would be in effect.<br>
<br>
<br>
All this is not fixed in stone, it will change over time, and any of the above rules may not apply at all to every situation. <br>
<br>
<br>
This is all I can think of right now, I’ll make edits as I think of other stuff, and as it is discussed and people make comments.<br>
